race.comment: CYCLONE SEBAS (1) pinged the lids from out wide but faded out of it late when 6th at Maitland in a Grade 5. Has a good record here at this journey. Strong form has emerged from his last run. Has ability and is a key runner. MAJESTIC TYSON (2) stalked the lead after a clean break from the tricky draw then burst clear to score (17.54) at this track in a Grade 4 over 300m. Has hit winning form and can go on with it. TOUT BELLE (8) stalked the lead after a clean break from the tricky draw and went on to finish second (17.51) at this track in a Grade 5 over 300m. Goes very well from this draw with two wins and three minor placings from five starts. Expected to feature. FLYING SAUCER (3) boasts a solid strike-rate over this trip.
